1
00:00:05,800 --> 00:00:08,496
<i>Press down hard on the gas</i>

2
00:00:08,569 --> 00:00:12,437
<i>That's right, there's no compromise</i>

3
00:00:12,506 --> 00:00:16,499
<i>We'll slip through the night</i>

4
00:00:16,844 --> 00:00:19,335
<i>At the final moment push hard</i>

5
00:00:19,413 --> 00:00:23,474
<i>That's right, all the way to zero,</i>

6
00:00:23,551 --> 00:00:27,510
<i>Until we wipe away the days</i>

7
00:00:28,989 --> 00:00:33,722
<i>Gently open your heart</i>

8
00:00:34,428 --> 00:00:37,397
<i>If you pull it close to you</i>

9
00:00:39,834 --> 00:00:41,927
<i>It will reach you, without a doubt</i>

10
00:00:42,670 --> 00:00:43,967
<i>It will come, closer</i>

11
00:00:44,305 --> 00:00:46,865
<i>Now</i>

12
00:00:54,915 --> 00:01:00,285
<i>We're speeding through life,</i>
<i>squeezing it for all of its worth</i>

13
00:01:00,488 --> 00:01:01,648
<i>Our feet are tied</i>

14
00:01:01,722 --> 00:01:05,522
<i>But we still keep going farther</i>

15
00:01:05,860 --> 00:01:11,059
<i>Even if I take it back, and grasp it</i>

16
00:01:11,332 --> 00:01:12,663
<i>If you're not the one</i>

17
00:01:12,733 --> 00:01:14,132
<i>There will be no meaning</i>

18
00:01:14,201 --> 00:01:20,470
<i>And so we'll go far off into the distance.</i>

19
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:33,007
Hey you, failure.

20
00:01:35,485 --> 00:01:37,578
I have two pieces
of advice for you.

21
00:01:38,588 --> 00:01:40,419
First, if you intend to call
yourself a Shinobi,

22
00:01:40,490 --> 00:01:41,787
stop that revolting cheering of yours.

23
00:01:43,460 --> 00:01:44,620
And second...

24
00:01:45,929 --> 00:01:48,329
a failure will
always be a failure.

25
00:01:48,932 --> 00:01:50,229
There's no changing that!

26
00:01:53,903 --> 00:01:55,268
Do you want to see about that?

27
00:02:03,646 --> 00:02:04,374
You!

28
00:02:04,914 --> 00:02:07,542
Naruto, I get where you're
coming from, believe me.

29
00:02:08,451 --> 00:02:11,750
But all fighting must be done
officially in a match!

30
00:02:13,123 --> 00:02:16,581
The failure beats the gifted genius
through sheer effort...

31
00:02:17,727 --> 00:02:19,388
Wouldn't that make for
an exciting main battle?

32
00:02:23,133 --> 00:02:24,760
<i>I promise you.</i>

33
00:02:34,110 --> 00:02:35,634
I will win no matter what!

34
00:02:45,088 --> 00:02:50,958
Gaara vs. Rock Lee:
The Power of Youth Explodes!

35
00:02:51,895 --> 00:02:52,862
Hey, Choji!

36
00:02:53,296 --> 00:02:54,490
You're in trouble.

37
00:02:54,964 --> 00:02:57,125
Only the strong ones are left.

38
00:02:58,368 --> 00:03:01,826
Probably the strongest of Hidden Sound
must be that bloke.

39
00:03:02,839 --> 00:03:05,831
And Lee is apparently strong
enough to take on Sasuke!

40
00:03:06,810 --> 00:03:08,675
And particularly that Sand guy!

41
00:03:09,646 --> 00:03:12,012
He's probably
the most dangerous one!

42
00:03:18,555 --> 00:03:20,386
I-I don't care!

43
00:03:20,690 --> 00:03:23,158
I plan to forfeit right away
if that happens...

44
00:03:23,426 --> 00:03:24,415
So that means...

45
00:03:24,527 --> 00:03:24,959
Huh?

46
00:03:25,028 --> 00:03:27,826
...you plan to forego
all you can eat BBQ, too, then.

47
00:03:27,931 --> 00:03:30,126
What? Come on!

48
00:03:31,801 --> 00:03:32,768
Don't worry.

49
00:03:33,002 --> 00:03:34,230
If things start getting ugly,

50
00:03:34,304 --> 00:03:38,104
I'll step in and stop the fight,
like I did for Hinata. Okay?

51
00:03:38,675 --> 00:03:40,233
Prime beef tongue, short ribs...

52
00:03:40,310 --> 00:03:42,676
- You can eat what you want.
- <i>Don't dangle food in front of him!</i>

53
00:03:43,346 --> 00:03:44,779
- <i>Besides he didn't step in...</i>
- You can eat whatever you want...

54
00:03:44,848 --> 00:03:46,577
- <i>and stop the fight for Hinata.</i>
- And all you want.

55
00:03:49,119 --> 00:03:56,025
B-B-Q! All right, B-B-Q!
All you can eat!

56
00:04:00,230 --> 00:04:01,959
<i>He doesn't look good.</i>

57
00:04:03,199 --> 00:04:04,757
<i>Watching the previous fight...</i>

58
00:04:05,702 --> 00:04:06,964
<i>Did it get stirred up?</i>

59
00:04:08,238 --> 00:04:10,798
<i>His inner demon!</i>

60
00:04:12,542 --> 00:04:14,908
<i>I'm curious about that guy, Neji, too...</i>

61
00:04:17,547 --> 00:04:18,980
<i>Here's a plan.</i>

62
00:04:21,217 --> 00:04:21,911
Kankuro?

63
00:04:22,018 --> 00:04:24,680
Just a little
information gathering mission.

64
00:04:26,456 --> 00:04:26,979
Hey!

65
00:04:27,190 --> 00:04:27,713
Huh?

66
00:04:28,258 --> 00:04:30,249
What are you doing here
all by yourself?

67
00:04:30,660 --> 00:04:32,924
Shouldn't you be with your friends?

68
00:04:33,429 --> 00:04:35,556
I-It's none of your business, is it?!

69
00:04:37,634 --> 00:04:39,534
<i>Hmmm. Well, well...</i>

70
00:04:40,637 --> 00:04:42,901
That guy... Neji Hyuga, right?

71
00:04:43,706 --> 00:04:45,333
Well, it seems to me that

72
00:04:45,408 --> 00:04:48,002
he didn't reveal the true extent
of his power in that last match.

73
00:04:48,244 --> 00:04:49,233
What's he about?

74
00:04:51,381 --> 00:04:53,315
I'm going to crush him!

75
00:04:55,451 --> 00:04:57,976
Err, that's not what
I was asking.

76
00:04:59,289 --> 00:05:01,951
<i>Besides, this guy's way out of his league...</i>

77
00:05:03,326 --> 00:05:06,693
You seem like a fun guy.
I quite like you.

78
00:05:07,163 --> 00:05:11,156
You're dull.
And I don't like you at all!

79
00:05:13,469 --> 00:05:16,029
<i>I'm going to waste this guy!</i>

80
00:05:19,042 --> 00:05:21,408
We will now resume the battle.

81
00:05:25,181 --> 00:05:26,011
Okay!

82
00:05:26,749 --> 00:05:30,344
You'll be up this time for sure.
Go for it, Lee!

83
00:05:31,221 --> 00:05:32,051
No!

84
00:05:32,222 --> 00:05:32,881
- Huh?
- What?

85
00:05:33,489 --> 00:05:38,290
Seeing as I've come this far,
I rather be the last!

86
00:05:40,597 --> 00:05:42,588
<i>Is Lee sulking?</i>

87
00:06:09,125 --> 00:06:11,525
Hurry up and get down here...

88
00:06:14,831 --> 00:06:16,355
Safe!

89
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:20,598
- Hey!
- Don't do anything misleading, idiot!

90
00:06:20,803 --> 00:06:22,896
Gaara vs. Rock Lee

91
00:06:24,140 --> 00:06:24,731
Oh! Lee!

92
00:06:26,643 --> 00:06:28,201
It worked!

93
00:06:28,845 --> 00:06:31,143
If you say you want to go last,
then you won't be last.

94
00:06:31,781 --> 00:06:33,772
It's an application of the same law

95
00:06:33,850 --> 00:06:36,444
that says a stone thrown to hit
a telephone pole will miss,

96
00:06:36,519 --> 00:06:39,420
and a stone thrown to miss
will be a direct hit!

97
00:06:39,689 --> 00:06:42,658
Right! That's my student!

98
00:06:42,825 --> 00:06:45,259
I absolutely did not
want to go last!

99
00:06:45,728 --> 00:06:47,992
I threw them a beauty of a curve!

100
00:06:48,931 --> 00:06:50,523
<i>Threw whom a curve?</i>

101
00:06:50,933 --> 00:06:54,391
Okay, so let me give you
a little piece of "nice" advice.

102
00:06:54,904 --> 00:06:55,598
Right!

103
00:06:56,873 --> 00:07:00,036
Probably no one has noticed yet, but...

104
00:07:00,943 --> 00:07:03,434
That gourd is suspicious!

105
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:05,104
I see!

106
00:07:05,715 --> 00:07:06,682
Quit with the notes!

107
00:07:07,050 --> 00:07:11,009
You're not going to have time to
read them during the match! Fool!

108
00:07:11,321 --> 00:07:12,117
I see!

109
00:07:13,823 --> 00:07:15,484
<i>He didn't realize that?</i>

110
00:07:16,626 --> 00:07:18,719
<i>Wow, is Lee going to be all right?</i>

111
00:07:18,928 --> 00:07:23,262
All right!
Go! Lee!

112
00:07:23,766 --> 00:07:25,290
Yeah!

113
00:07:34,010 --> 00:07:37,309
I am very happy to be squaring
off with you so early in the match.

114
00:07:42,585 --> 00:07:45,986
I don't know what kind of moves
that bowl cut guy has,

115
00:07:46,389 --> 00:07:48,118
but he will never take Gaara.

116
00:07:49,025 --> 00:07:49,923
Never!

117
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:55,254
<i>He's fast, to be sure,</i>
<i>but his kick is not all that great.</i>

118
00:07:56,232 --> 00:07:56,891
No...

119
00:08:08,711 --> 00:08:11,179
He's... strong.

120
00:08:16,219 --> 00:08:17,686
Please don't be in such a hurry.

121
00:08:24,127 --> 00:08:24,889
<i>Lee...</i>

122
00:08:28,364 --> 00:08:30,832
<i>Be careful, Lee.</i>

123
00:08:35,905 --> 00:08:38,703
Now then... The 9th match...

124
00:08:41,677 --> 00:08:42,405
Begin!

125
00:08:46,582 --> 00:08:48,482
Leaf Hurricane!

126
00:09:06,202 --> 00:09:07,134
Is that...?

127
00:09:07,437 --> 00:09:07,994
Sand?

128
00:09:08,871 --> 00:09:10,099
<i>What an unusual Jutsu...</i>

129
00:09:10,673 --> 00:09:13,574
<i>There's sand in his gourd!</i>

130
00:09:14,544 --> 00:09:15,272
<i>That's...</i>

131
00:09:19,782 --> 00:09:21,010
<i>That's it?</i>

132
00:09:22,552 --> 00:09:24,247
<i>Desert Coffin!</i>

133
00:09:34,263 --> 00:09:35,730
<i>Desert Burial!</i>

134
00:09:39,068 --> 00:09:41,662
<i>Not another horror story like that...</i>

135
00:09:42,805 --> 00:09:44,864
<i>A sand manipulating Jutsu, eh?</i>

136
00:09:45,541 --> 00:09:46,633
<i>Sounds like trouble.</i>

137
00:09:47,643 --> 00:09:49,668
<i>But let's give it a go!</i>

138
00:10:17,573 --> 00:10:20,133
Even that Lee's fast strikes...

139
00:10:20,243 --> 00:10:21,676
have no effect at all!

140
00:10:22,044 --> 00:10:24,205
What's the deal?!

141
00:10:24,747 --> 00:10:28,239
No physical strike is going to
have any effect on him.

142
00:10:28,417 --> 00:10:28,940
What?

143
00:10:29,285 --> 00:10:31,276
The Sand shields and protects Gaara

144
00:10:31,654 --> 00:10:34,521
on its own accord, independently
of any intent on Gaara's part.

145
00:10:35,791 --> 00:10:39,454
That's why... no one has been able
to do it so far...

146
00:10:40,963 --> 00:10:44,296
Injure Gaara, that is.

147
00:10:47,737 --> 00:10:51,537
<i>Curses! He's not moving</i>
<i>a muscle and still...!</i>

148
00:10:52,675 --> 00:10:53,801
Is that it?

149
00:10:55,978 --> 00:10:58,606
Entertain me a bit more...

150
00:11:00,650 --> 00:11:01,912
There's not enough yet!

151
00:11:04,153 --> 00:11:04,710
Blood!

152
00:11:20,202 --> 00:11:22,830
Why is Lee only using Taijutsu?

153
00:11:23,406 --> 00:11:25,397
He'll never be able to get close
enough for that!

154
00:11:26,042 --> 00:11:29,273
Why doesn't he step back a bit and
use Ninjutsu or something?

155
00:11:30,546 --> 00:11:31,979
It's not that he doesn't use it.

156
00:11:32,882 --> 00:11:33,906
He can't use it.

157
00:11:34,584 --> 00:11:34,948
Huh?

158
00:11:35,585 --> 00:11:39,578
Lee has almost no Ninjutsu
or Genjutsu skills.

159
00:11:40,189 --> 00:11:41,383
N-No way!

160
00:11:42,725 --> 00:11:46,593
When I first met Lee,
he was completely inept.

161
00:11:46,929 --> 00:11:48,556
He had no talent whatsoever.

162
00:11:49,599 --> 00:11:51,829
What? I can't believe that!

163
00:12:20,216 --> 00:12:21,080
Hey hey!

164
00:12:31,994 --> 00:12:32,824
Certainly...

165
00:12:33,329 --> 00:12:37,425
A ninja who can't do Ninjutsu
and Genjutsu is a rarity.

166
00:12:39,034 --> 00:12:46,236
That's why, the only path open to Lee
as a Ninja was Taijutsu.

167
00:12:47,509 --> 00:12:50,239
But! That's precisely what
makes him a winner!

168
00:12:50,579 --> 00:12:51,102
Huh?

169
00:12:51,747 --> 00:12:53,112
Lee, take them off!

170
00:12:54,617 --> 00:12:56,482
B-But Guy Sensei!

171
00:12:56,785 --> 00:12:59,151
You told me only to do that

172
00:12:59,221 --> 00:13:00,882
to protect a large group
of very important people!

173
00:13:01,257 --> 00:13:02,554
That's quite all right!

174
00:13:02,892 --> 00:13:04,120
I give you permission!

175
00:13:13,869 --> 00:13:14,801
Are those...?

176
00:13:15,304 --> 00:13:16,293
Weights?

177
00:13:17,139 --> 00:13:18,902
<i>That's some cliché training...</i>

178
00:13:19,141 --> 00:13:20,233
I see!

179
00:13:20,743 --> 00:13:21,402
Ridiculous!

180
00:13:23,812 --> 00:13:27,111
All right, now I can
move easily!

181
00:13:27,783 --> 00:13:31,219
<i>Humph! Does he think</i>
<i>removing some measly little weights</i>

182
00:13:31,287 --> 00:13:33,687
<i>is going to enable him to</i>
<i>outmaneuver Gaara's sand...?</i>

183
00:13:40,062 --> 00:13:42,030
<i>A bit extreme, I'd say, Guy.</i>

184
00:13:44,466 --> 00:13:46,525
Go, Lee!

185
00:13:46,602 --> 00:13:47,569
Right!

186
00:14:02,785 --> 00:14:03,308
Go!

187
00:14:04,820 --> 00:14:05,377
Very close!

188
00:14:06,088 --> 00:14:06,782
<i>Fast!</i>

189
00:14:07,323 --> 00:14:08,051
<i>Amazing...!</i>

190
00:14:14,763 --> 00:14:17,664
Because he can't use
Ninjutsu or Genjutsu...

191
00:14:18,334 --> 00:14:21,895
Therefore, he channeled all
of his time,

192
00:14:22,071 --> 00:14:24,232
all of his energy and...

193
00:14:24,640 --> 00:14:27,131
all of his being into Taijutsu.

194
00:14:28,777 --> 00:14:31,644
Though he can't do any other Jutsu...

195
00:14:32,281 --> 00:14:34,215
He won't lose to anyone...

196
00:14:34,950 --> 00:14:37,009
He is a Taijutsu specialist!

197
00:14:50,299 --> 00:14:53,132
<i>I can't believe it!</i>
<i>Gaara's been injured!</i>

198
00:14:54,336 --> 00:14:55,234
<i>No way...!</i>

199
00:14:55,971 --> 00:14:59,463
Bushy Brows is even
faster than before!

200
00:15:00,376 --> 00:15:02,640
Was he this strong?!

201
00:15:03,412 --> 00:15:08,850
Youth is... explosion!

202
00:15:08,917 --> 00:15:10,179
Right!

203
00:15:18,761 --> 00:15:19,750
Over here!

204
00:15:24,533 --> 00:15:25,158
Good!

205
00:15:26,602 --> 00:15:27,967
<i>I got him good!</i>

206
00:15:28,771 --> 00:15:30,898
A-Amazing, he's so fast!

207
00:15:31,573 --> 00:15:33,598
The Sand Shield can't keep
up with him!

208
00:15:34,410 --> 00:15:35,399
A direct hit!

209
00:15:35,811 --> 00:15:37,506
A-Amazing.

210
00:15:37,880 --> 00:15:39,347
His strikes are lightning fast!

211
00:15:40,149 --> 00:15:42,481
I can't even track him
with my eyes!

212
00:15:54,063 --> 00:15:55,052
Uh oh...

213
00:15:55,297 --> 00:15:56,992
Uh oh is right!

214
00:15:57,066 --> 00:16:01,059
That black circles under the eye
guy is taking some serious blows!

215
00:16:01,370 --> 00:16:03,065
That's not what I meant.

216
00:16:03,439 --> 00:16:03,928
Huh?

217
00:16:21,223 --> 00:16:22,417
W-What the...?!

218
00:16:22,791 --> 00:16:25,282
His face is crumbling right off!

219
00:16:26,061 --> 00:16:27,756
<i>His whole body is covered</i>
<i>with sand...</i>

220
00:16:28,163 --> 00:16:29,687
There's not a scratch on him!

221
00:16:30,132 --> 00:16:32,032
W-What's with this guy?!

222
00:16:36,939 --> 00:16:39,169
<i>Sure enough, he was</i>
<i>encased in sand, eh.</i>

223
00:16:40,342 --> 00:16:42,640
<i>But, it's been a long time since</i>

224
00:16:42,711 --> 00:16:44,770
<i>I've seen that expression</i>
<i>on Gaara's face.</i>

225
00:16:46,448 --> 00:16:49,315
<i>I felt that he was becoming</i>
<i>more and more unstable</i>

226
00:16:49,384 --> 00:16:51,909
<i>as the Chunin Exam progressed...</i>

227
00:16:54,389 --> 00:16:57,586
<i>So Gaara's other self has</i>
<i>been awakened, eh?</i>

228
00:17:02,231 --> 00:17:04,358
Hey! What is that?

229
00:17:04,833 --> 00:17:08,394
That protected him
against Bushy Brow's strikes?

230
00:17:08,604 --> 00:17:11,368
Yes... It's Sand Armor.

231
00:17:11,974 --> 00:17:12,702
Armor?

232
00:17:13,275 --> 00:17:16,176
Ordinarily, the Sand Shield
functions to protect him automatically,

233
00:17:16,612 --> 00:17:19,172
but, if by chance,
the Shield is penetrated,

234
00:17:19,648 --> 00:17:21,843
the Sand Armor functions as a second
layer of protection against strikes...

235
00:17:22,584 --> 00:17:25,576
That's Gaara's... absolute defense!

236
00:17:26,021 --> 00:17:28,546
Well then, there's no way
to get him!

237
00:17:29,057 --> 00:17:30,649
He doesn't have any weak points.

238
00:17:31,593 --> 00:17:33,857
<i>No. That's not entirely true...</i>

239
00:17:34,963 --> 00:17:37,864
<i>The Sand Armor is actually</i>
<i>riddled with weak points.</i>

240
00:17:39,101 --> 00:17:42,195
<i>First of all, because it's not automatic,</i>
<i>it uses up a lot of Chakra.</i>

241
00:17:42,838 --> 00:17:44,965
<i>It's also less effective</i>
<i>than the Sand Shield,</i>

242
00:17:45,040 --> 00:17:47,338
<i>and it takes an enormous amount</i>
<i>of physical energy</i>

243
00:17:47,409 --> 00:17:49,343
<i>to keep the sand clinging</i>
<i>to the body like that.</i>

244
00:17:50,679 --> 00:17:56,140
<i>Gaara's having to use the armor...</i>
<i>is proof that he's under pressure.</i>

245
00:17:57,352 --> 00:18:00,549
<i>That Lee is really good...</i>

246
00:18:01,757 --> 00:18:03,918
<i>But, the outcome of the match</i>
<i>is already a given.</i>

247
00:18:05,127 --> 00:18:07,925
<i>He will never beat Gaara!</i>

248
00:18:09,364 --> 00:18:10,388
Is that all?

249
00:18:12,134 --> 00:18:13,658
<i>But what an incredible</i>
<i>defense he has...</i>

250
00:18:14,369 --> 00:18:17,930
<i>no amount of speed is going</i>
<i>to let me get a strike through.</i>

251
00:18:19,074 --> 00:18:23,943
<i>I'll have to do major damage</i>
<i>from above the sand guard.</i>

252
00:18:25,747 --> 00:18:26,543
<i>That will be Lotus!</i>

253
00:18:31,053 --> 00:18:31,678
Yes.

254
00:18:46,001 --> 00:18:46,797
Be ready!

255
00:18:52,574 --> 00:18:55,668
<i>A thin sand guard like that</i>
<i>will be inconsequential</i>

256
00:18:56,245 --> 00:18:59,646
<i>in the face of Lee's high speed</i>
<i>Lotus slamming down from above.</i>

257
00:19:01,483 --> 00:19:02,973
Hurry up and bring it on!

258
00:19:03,518 --> 00:19:05,315
You asked for it!

259
00:19:08,957 --> 00:19:09,981
He didn't float.

260
00:19:10,292 --> 00:19:11,281
Not just yet!

261
00:19:19,234 --> 00:19:20,826
What an amazing series of kicks!

262
00:19:23,672 --> 00:19:27,574
<i>Even an ordinary Lotus has</i>
<i>a tremendous strain on the body...!</i>

263
00:19:28,010 --> 00:19:29,637
<i>Lee, let this be the finishing blow!</i>

264
00:19:43,659 --> 00:19:45,524
Take this!

265
00:19:47,596 --> 00:19:49,223
Primary Lotus!

266
00:20:16,591 --> 00:20:17,489
I got him...

267
00:20:18,427 --> 00:20:19,086
good!

268
00:20:21,029 --> 00:20:22,553
Right on!

269
00:20:22,898 --> 00:20:24,593
I-It's over!

270
00:20:24,833 --> 00:20:26,767
W-What? This can't be!

271
00:20:27,035 --> 00:20:29,833
He did it! Lee's won!

272
00:20:30,372 --> 00:20:33,000
Hey, he isn't dead, is he?

273
00:20:42,384 --> 00:20:42,941
Wha?!

274
00:20:47,556 --> 00:20:48,181
Huh?!

275
00:21:00,802 --> 00:21:01,598
What?!

276
00:21:05,756 --> 00:21:10,216
<i>Hey, can you hear it?</i>

277
00:21:10,361 --> 00:21:18,700
<i>The clear, blue sky goes on and on</i>

278
00:21:19,703 --> 00:21:28,372
<i>The ocean spans limitlessly</i>

279
00:21:28,779 --> 00:21:36,618
<i>Please keep that smile on your face forever</i>

280
00:21:37,888 --> 00:21:43,292
<i>Or else I'll cry</i>

281
00:21:43,360 --> 00:21:47,387
<i>You won't have to search around you</i>

282
00:21:47,464 --> 00:21:51,025
<i>It's all ok now.</i>

283
00:21:51,368 --> 00:21:59,901
<i>Everyone is inside</i>
<i>this hand</i>

284
00:22:00,177 --> 00:22:05,376
<i>when you want to cry,</i>
<i>and you want to run away</i>

285
00:22:05,449 --> 00:22:09,852
<i>When you forget what happiness is</i>

286
00:22:09,920 --> 00:22:13,686
<i>Just sing.</i>

287
00:22:13,924 --> 00:22:19,089
<i>Light is born, and darkness was born</i>

288
00:22:19,163 --> 00:22:21,358
<i>The two are one</i>

289
00:22:21,465 --> 00:22:27,734
<i>Harmonia, feel the telepathy</i>

290
00:22:28,238 --> 00:22:33,335
<i>Hey, can you hear it?</i>

291
00:22:37,612 --> 00:22:39,842
Hey, what happened, Bushy-Brows?!

292
00:22:40,081 --> 00:22:42,242
All of your strength seems
to have disappeared!

293
00:22:42,383 --> 00:22:45,011
You're going to be destroyed
at this rate!

294
00:22:45,453 --> 00:22:49,321
But, hey, Bushy-Brows is smiling

295
00:22:50,024 --> 00:22:51,616
How can he continue to keep up
a fighting stance

296
00:22:51,693 --> 00:22:53,524
when he's being routed like this?!

297
00:22:54,429 --> 00:22:59,264
Next episode: "Lee's Hidden Strength:
Forbidden Secret Jutsu!"

298
00:22:59,801 --> 00:23:02,599
The expression in Bushy Brows' eyes
has changed!
